race.comment: MAYFAIR (3) bounced back at Newcastle with a tough effort outside the lead, sticking on gamely to just miss the placings. On the quick back-up, he looks set to peak and should appreciate being ridden with more cover. Shapes as the one to beat. GREEN SHADOWS (8) is racing better than his form suggests and will relish some give in the ground. With Collett aboard under a light weight and blinkers back on, he maps to get the perfect run and is a big chance to end a long drought. SIR ARTIE (6) was well supported in Listed grade last start but didn't finish off when ridden forward. The inside draw likely forces similar tactics, but his best is certainly good enough to feature. TICKLEBELLY (11) showed grit winning the Snake Gully Cup at Gundagai. This is tougher, yet she should give herself every chance again on speed. KINTYRE (5) has built steadily into this prep but faces a wide draw. Still, he's capable and worth keeping safe.
